    "created_at": "2014-08-25T00:13:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-25T00:13:58Z",
    "body": "As I [commented on the PR](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/15411#issuecomment-48094933) and as [the code says](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/libserialize/serialize.rs#L555-L558), the encoding aspect is meant to not fail, but rather to return an error (because the encodable/decodable context allows it to). It is was a stopgap until we could have custom error strings for any encoder (as we can do now).\n\nAs noted, previous PRs to add `Show` have been declined for now due to the fallibility of `RefCell`. That said, I am sympathetic to any structure containing a `RefCell` basically doesn't work with `#[deriving]`, which is quite unfortunate.\n",
